version: 1
display_name: PHTN-50-000185 - The Photon operating system must enforce a delay of at least four seconds between logon prompts following a failed logon attempt in login.defs.
global_description: |-
  Limiting the number of logon attempts over a certain time interval reduces the chances that an unauthorized user may gain access to an account.
osfinger:
  - VMware Photon OS-5
refs:
  disa_stig:
    - PHTN-50-000185
  srg:
    - SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00226
  cci:
    - CCI-000366
  nist:
    - CM-6 b
benchmark_id:
  vcf9_photon_5:
    type: custom
    desc: The Photon operating system must enforce a delay of at least four seconds between logon prompts following a failed logon attempt in login.defs.
    control_id: PHTN-50-000185
    scored: true
    profile:
      - default
    information: |-
      At the command line, run the following command to verify a four second delay is configured between logon attempts:

      # grep '^FAIL_DELAY' /etc/login.defs

      Example result:

      FAIL_DELAY 4

      If the "FAIL_DELAY" option is not set to 4 or more, is missing or commented out, this is a finding.
    rationale: |-
      Limiting the number of logon attempts over a certain time interval reduces the chances that an unauthorized user may gain access to an account.
    remediation: |-
      Navigate to and open:

      /etc/login.defs

      Add or update the following line:

      FAIL_DELAY 4
